WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 777
Chapter 777
(House Bill 753)
AN ACT concerning
Tax Sales – Homeowner Protections – Revisions
FOR the purpose of requiring the State Tax Sale Ombudsman to develop a process to allow
a homeowner to designate a family member or another representative of the
homeowner to communicate and work with the Ombudsman on the homeowner’s
behalf; requiring the dwelling of a homeowner to be withheld from tax sale if the
homeowner has a documented terminal illness or medical hardship; increasing the
maximum value of a dwelling that a homeowner may reside in and be eligible for the
Homeowner Protection Program; requiring homeowners with terminal illness or
medical hardship to receive priority for enrollment in the Homeowner Protection
Program; and generally relating to protections for homeowners in tax sale.
BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
Article – Tax – Property
Section 2–112(b) and (e), 14–811(i) and (j), 14–836(a) and (b)(4)(i)3., 14–883, and
14–884
